# GPU Troubleshooting Notes

## Issue: Black screen after GRUB
- Fix: Installed correct drivers for the GPU
- Notes: Some distros require manual driver installation

## Issue: Screen tearing
- Fix: Enabled compositor settings and adjusted refresh rate

## Issue: GPU not detected
- Fix: Reseated GPU, checked power cables, updated BIOS
- Notes first GPU slot bad connection, moved to second slot, one remaining.

GPU issues taught me how Linux handles drivers differently across distros. How bad connections with GPU can cause uncommand problems. 
